  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nThis issue hosts a feature request to re-implement certain functionality as procedural macros so they are `#[derive]`-able.\r\n\r\n1. `ssz` serde\r\n2. `TestRandom` impl\r\n\r\n## Present Behaviour\r\n\r\nWe have to derive each of these by hand and it puts higher burden on the maintainer/author.\r\n\r\n## Expected Behaviour\r\n\r\nWould be great to do something like:\r\n\r\n```rust\r\n#[derive(ssz, test_random)]\r\nstruct BeaconState {\r\n    // ...\r\n}\r\n```\r\n## Steps to resolve\r\n\r\nImplement the desired functionality; is a great use case for the new procedural macro support in Rust 2018.\r\n\r\nThis task is lower priority than getting the codebase up to spec but figured I would raise this in case anyone has some spare cycles.",
